The annual Miss South Africa contest is underway as the top 30 contestants will be revealed live on the Miss South Africa app on Monday, May 16 at 7pm. The beauty pageant is a leadership platform for young and ambitious South African women. According to the Miss South Africa group, the panel includes former judge and Miss SA 2015, Liesl Laurie-Mthombeni, body positive activist Tracey-Lee Lusty Horwitz, business dynamo Koo Govender, fashion designer Khosi Nkosi, businesswoman and award-winning editor Makhosazana Zwane-Siguqa, actor Simon√© Nortmann and actor and TV personality Thando Thabethe.